# Spark — iOS Native (Cursor root rules)
# iOS 17+ · Xcode 16+ · Swift 6 · SwiftUI + UIKit hybrid

## Stack
- Swift 6 strict concurrency; no Swift 5 concurrency workarounds
- SwiftUI primary; UIKit only when SwiftUI cannot (wrap with *Representable)
- SPM only; URLSession + async/await for networking (no third-party HTTP libs)
- SwiftData + Keychain; Repository pattern for all data sources

## Architecture
- TCA or MVVM + Clean Architecture: Domain | Data | Presentation
- @Observable (iOS 17+), not ObservableObject; @Environment for DI (no singletons)
- Typed routes with NavigationStack; no NavigationView or @EnvironmentObject
- Business logic unit-testable without UI; no force-unwrap in production

## Concurrency
- Structured concurrency only; @MainActor for UI; actors for shared mutable state
- Never DispatchQueue.main.async or .sync on main thread

## Code generation defaults
- Full files with imports; #Preview on every View file
- os.Logger not print(); max ~300 lines per file; public APIs need ///
- Prefer semantic colors, Dynamic Type, VoiceOver, Light/Dark, zh-Hans + en localization

## Modular rules (see .cursor/rules/)
- ios-foundation.mdc — always on
- ios-swiftui.mdc — Swift / SwiftUI files
- ios-module-scaffold.mdc — new feature modules ({MODULE_NAME})
- ios-design-system.mdc — Views / UI polish
- ios-performance.mdc — perf work

Persona / role prompt: use Cursor Settings → Rules for AI (or project user rules), not duplicated here.
